WEBVTT

00:00.802 --> 00:03.268
Welcome to the James River Church Podcast.

00:03.288 --> 00:06.978
You're about to hear another inspirational message from Pastor John Lindell.

00:06.998 --> 00:09.164
Lead pastor at James River Church.

00:09.184 --> 00:13.234
It's our prayer that this message is an encouragement and blessing to your life.

00:14.466 --> 00:16.569
And you're watching for the very first time.

00:16.909 --> 00:19.312
We're in a series on the book of James.

00:19.672 --> 00:21.955
And James is such a fantastic book.

00:22.355 --> 00:27.462
It's actually one of the easiest books in the New Testament to apply to our lives.

00:28.022 --> 00:30.405
And it really is kind of Christianity 101.

00:30.786 --> 00:36.332
So what you have in James is you have the basics, which is why we've called the series The Essentials.

00:37.734 --> 00:44.402
James' concern is for you and I to have a living, vibrant, active,

00:44.898 --> 00:56.750
When it comes to our Christianity, he wants us to be the kind of Christian that when people look at us, they say he or she, they're the real deal.

00:56.770 --> 01:11.986
And so what James does is he presents for us a series of tests in his book by which you and I can evaluate our progress in the Christian journey, by which you and I can evaluate

01:12.066 --> 01:14.710
our maturity in the Christian life.

01:15.050 --> 01:16.573
And so we've looked at two tests.

01:16.593 --> 01:18.736
We looked at the test of trials.

01:19.117 --> 01:21.801
Last week we looked at the test of temptation.

01:22.482 --> 01:30.053
And this morning James gives us the test of how you and I respond to the word of God.

01:31.295 --> 01:35.862
You know, I was thinking just about how valuable the word of God is and what it does in our life.

01:35.922 --> 01:38.706
And it reminded me of a story I'd come across

01:39.458 --> 01:47.930
It was about a guy named Rob Cutshaw, who was a rock collector and owned a little roadside shop outside of Andrews, North Carolina.

01:47.970 --> 01:55.340
And like many in the trade, he would go out and hunt for rocks and then would sell them to collectors or to jewelers.

01:56.101 --> 02:05.193
He didn't know a lot about rocks just enough to find them and then to leave them with an appraiser or to offer them to other people.

02:06.175 --> 02:08.658
While on a dig in 1967,

02:08.770 --> 02:12.675
Rob found a rock that he described as pretty and big.

02:13.736 --> 02:22.827
He unsuccessfully tried to sell the rock for $500, but when that failed, he placed the rock in his closet and left it there.

02:22.847 --> 02:38.066
20 years later, Rob found out that the rock he had tried to sell for a few hundred dollars was, in fact, the largest and most valuable sapphire ever found.

02:38.754 --> 02:42.600
Today, that rock weighs nearly one pound.

02:43.001 --> 02:50.613
It is known as the star of David Sapphire and is valued at $3 million.

02:51.976 --> 02:55.682
For 20 years, Rob did not realize what he had.

02:56.643 --> 03:03.314
And I tell that story because I think it's very easy for Christians to forget the value of the Word of God.

03:03.970 --> 03:10.485
to forget how important the word of God is, to forget what the word of God can do in all of our lives.

03:10.846 --> 03:18.785
Listen, the word of God is so powerful, it has the power to change a person's life at the most important point of their life.

03:19.066 --> 03:22.514
It can move a person from headed to hell to headed to heaven.

03:22.562 --> 03:25.846
It can take a person from darkness in the light.

03:25.926 --> 03:29.070
The Word of God is so exceptionally powerful.

03:29.490 --> 03:31.333
It can grow us in our faith.

03:31.713 --> 03:32.955
It can make us mature.

03:33.435 --> 03:39.803
It can give us authority to do supernatural things in the name of Jesus.

03:41.165 --> 03:48.754
But if the Word of God is going to do that in our lives, then we must respond to it correctly.

03:49.410 --> 03:54.018
And that's exactly what James is talking about in James chapter one.

03:54.078 --> 04:02.993
Now, as you come here, this is the third test in the book, as I said, and it's a test on how you and I respond to the word of God.

04:03.454 --> 04:06.900
And James features or talks about two areas specifically.

04:06.960 --> 04:09.925
The first is how you and I receive the word of God.

04:11.027 --> 04:15.314
And the second is how we react or how we respond to the word of God.

04:16.002 --> 04:24.210
So let's look at what James says about how you and I are to receive the word because a true Christian receives the word.

04:24.590 --> 04:26.673
James chapter one, verse 19.

04:27.633 --> 04:36.442
Understand this, my dear brothers and sisters, you must all be quick to listen.

04:37.924 --> 04:44.370
What I think is notable in this is that it doesn't matter where you are in your journey with Christ.

04:45.218 --> 04:47.402
It doesn't matter if you've been doing this for 40 years.

04:47.822 --> 04:50.006
It doesn't matter if you just started last week.

04:51.588 --> 04:53.992
It doesn't matter if you're a child.

04:54.433 --> 04:56.396
It doesn't matter if you're a teenager.

04:56.717 --> 04:58.600
It doesn't matter if you're a college student.

04:58.960 --> 05:01.805
It doesn't matter if you're single, if you're married.

05:02.206 --> 05:03.928
It doesn't matter if you're a preacher.

05:04.269 --> 05:09.938
I mean, everybody is to be quick to listen.

05:11.234 --> 05:14.559
And remember James is writing about the Word of God.

05:14.859 --> 05:21.870
He mentions in verse 18, we were changed eternally by the Word of God.

05:22.371 --> 05:23.532
We were given new birth.

05:23.572 --> 05:25.275
We were given birth through the Word of God.

05:25.856 --> 05:33.347
And the idea is since we know the Word of God is powerful enough to turn us into a new creation.

05:34.909 --> 05:40.818
We should pay attention to it so it can continue to work in us.

05:42.658 --> 05:47.083
Let's not fall into the trap of thinking the only thing that matters in salvation.

05:47.383 --> 05:48.625
Does salvation matter?

05:48.645 --> 05:48.985
Yes.

05:49.786 --> 05:56.393
But there's a lot of Christians who are satisfied to stop at getting saved.

05:57.955 --> 06:05.944
Forgetting all the while that we are saved on purpose with the purpose and that purpose starts now and continues through eternity.

06:06.765 --> 06:11.570
Praise God you're saved, but don't stay a baby Christian the rest of your life.

06:12.738 --> 06:19.865
So we need to be careful how we respond to the word, that we pay attention to it, that we desire it.

06:20.105 --> 06:27.853
Peter will say in 1 Peter chapter two, earnestly, as newborn babes earnestly desire the pure milk of the word.

06:29.174 --> 06:30.095
It's the same idea.

06:30.115 --> 06:36.961
In fact, there's a lot of similarities between what James writes and what Peter writes in his epistle, 1 Peter.

06:38.123 --> 06:41.746
So ask yourself, are you quick to hear the word of God?

06:43.074 --> 06:46.299
Do you hunger for the Word in your life?

06:47.600 --> 06:55.292
Do you long to grow in your understanding of the Word and not only your understanding of the Word, but your application of the Word?

06:56.974 --> 06:59.738
Are you eager to hear it preached, taught?

07:00.739 --> 07:04.745
Are you eager to read it, to pick up your Bible at home?

07:05.466 --> 07:08.250
James says, be quick to listen.

07:09.111 --> 07:10.994
And then he goes on and he says this,

07:11.234 --> 07:15.920
You must be quick to listen, slow to speak.

07:17.222 --> 07:22.869
Now, a lot of times we read that on the surface, we're like, well, wow, what great advice we all talk, some of us talk too much.

07:23.910 --> 07:36.466
And the writer of Proverbs warns about that with verses like he regards his lips, guards his life, and even a foolish thought wise, if he keeps silent.

07:36.802 --> 07:41.648
I think another one is that in the abundance of words, there's much folly.

07:42.109 --> 07:44.912
But James isn't talking about people who talk too much.

07:46.114 --> 07:48.837
He's talking about how you and I receive the word.

07:49.918 --> 08:05.618
And we have to be careful that when we're hearing the word, that we don't water down the word, deny the word, or misinterpret the word because we wanna give our two cents.

08:07.170 --> 08:16.882
It's a little bit like what James warns us in James chapter three and verse one, let not many of you become teachers because teachers will be judged more harshly.

08:16.922 --> 08:22.469
So anytime we feel we're competent to comment on the word, what we're saying is we can live the word.

08:23.451 --> 08:35.666
But a greater concern to me in our society is simply this, a lot of people rather than accepting the authority of the word and rather than being quick to listen, slow to speak, they're like, well, you know, I don't see it that way.

08:37.058 --> 08:46.539
I believe this, or I feel this way, as if somehow their opinion is an authority greater than the authority of the Word of God.

08:47.742 --> 08:49.586
This is where you and I in

08:49.794 --> 08:55.101
in receiving the word of God, have to have the humility to say, he's God, I'm not.

08:55.181 --> 08:58.425
And what he says is what I'm gonna listen to.

08:58.745 --> 09:15.867
So if he says something different than I like, if he says something different than I've always believed, if he says something that's gonna mean I'm gonna have to change my life, then he wins all ties because he's God and it's his word and it's the rule for my life.

09:16.808 --> 09:18.450
I follow the word.

09:19.554 --> 09:24.420
Then it says, and be slow to get angry.

09:25.702 --> 09:27.785
In other words, don't get upset at the Word of God.

09:28.626 --> 09:44.626
If it confronts something in your life, maybe if it confronts a tradition or a value that you've held, but now you're finding out, or it impinges on your own desire, if it confronts you at the point of giving your finances,

09:46.338 --> 09:55.048
I know some people get very upset when you talk about tithing and do all kinds of gymnastics theologically to try to get out of paying a tithe.

09:55.429 --> 10:00.555
And they want to shift it to, well, you know, it's the preacher who wants money and is talking about money all the time.

10:00.815 --> 10:07.222
When it doesn't have anything to do with that, it's clear in the Bible that you and I are just tithe, but people get angry about it.

10:08.444 --> 10:10.226
Or people are living together.

10:10.306 --> 10:15.731
in a relationship outside of marriage, they're sexually active with one another.

10:15.771 --> 10:18.774
And then you say, listen, the word of God says you can't do that.

10:21.136 --> 10:24.519
And they go home and one or the others upset about it.

10:25.260 --> 10:28.743
Like where does he get off telling me I can't do this or I can't do that.

10:29.044 --> 10:34.629
What's happening in that moment is they're angry about the word of God.

10:35.850 --> 10:38.052
The Greek word there is the word or gate.

10:38.072 --> 10:39.954
We get our word ogre from it.

10:41.922 --> 10:48.851
The idea is enraged, violent, passionate wrath.

10:49.832 --> 10:53.116
Some people get very hostile when they hear the word of God.

10:54.378 --> 11:01.547
Sometimes people, because I have people tell me this, they say, you know, we brought somebody in the neighborhood home and said, that preacher looking to me the whole time.

11:02.048 --> 11:03.890
And so in a

11:04.002 --> 11:06.165
congregation of this size.

11:06.245 --> 11:12.775
I'm not saying I don't see individuals, I'm just saying for a person to feel that it's the Holy Spirit talking to them, but they can get angry.

11:13.917 --> 11:17.863
And James is saying, don't reject the word of God, receive it.

11:18.223 --> 11:18.584
Why?

11:18.624 --> 11:27.176
Verse 20, for man's anger does not bring about the righteous life that God desires.

11:29.099 --> 11:30.962
Here's the thing, anytime you and I,

11:32.162 --> 11:33.944
Hold the word of God at arm's length.

11:34.124 --> 11:49.183
If we get upset about what the Bible is saying, it circumvents the work of God in our life and keeps him from producing things in us that would ultimately not only bless us, but bless people around us.

11:50.705 --> 11:57.574
James goes on to say this in verse 21, therefore get rid of all the moral filth and the evil that is so prevalent.

11:58.475 --> 12:00.978
It's interesting that word for filth

12:01.090 --> 12:04.173
The root word speaks of wax in the ear.

12:05.854 --> 12:11.640
And if you have a bunch of wax in your ear, besides being discussing what happens, you can't hear.

12:12.861 --> 12:13.962
Do you see the analogy?

12:14.142 --> 12:18.166
A dirty life, a filthy life, plugs up your hearing.

12:19.908 --> 12:25.793
A lot of people can't hear the word of God, and they can hear it, but it's like it just falls off them.

12:25.873 --> 12:30.898
It's like they have this shell that the word of God can't penetrate

12:31.010 --> 12:34.514
and that shell is the unrighteousness of their life.

12:37.016 --> 12:48.047
It's their unwillingness to walk in a repentance that tenderizes their heart and opens them up not only to the word of God, but the work of God through the word in their life.

12:49.308 --> 12:58.898
Verse 21, James says, therefore get rid of all the moral filth and the evil that is so prevalent and he's talking here about the evil in the world.

13:01.474 --> 13:11.166
You know, here's the danger, and we mention it, but this is a very significant thing for believers to consider.

13:11.706 --> 13:17.373
Our world is increasingly becoming more and more wicked, more and more sensual.

13:19.255 --> 13:20.537
There's more and more evil.

13:21.638 --> 13:28.146
The preoccupation that the entertainment industry has with the demonic

13:29.922 --> 13:32.386
I mean, it's just unbelievable.

13:33.709 --> 13:42.524
And what happens is Christians can become numb to that evil and actually find themselves not only tolerating it, but embracing it.

13:44.026 --> 13:53.202
And what happens is, especially with things like social media and other things that I would suggest push groupthink

13:54.914 --> 13:59.780
and cause people to get caught up in the opinions of the world, the thinking of the world.

14:01.482 --> 14:10.332
So what happens is we become so much like the world that you can't tell the difference between the church and the world or Christians and the world.

14:11.613 --> 14:20.223
And James says we gotta get rid of the evil that's so prevalent and humbly accept the word planted in you which can save you.

14:21.064 --> 14:22.706
Do you realize that salvation, God,

14:22.978 --> 14:26.643
you are transformed by the living and enduring word of God at salvation.

14:26.663 --> 14:31.871
So it's the word that saved you, then the word is planted in you.

14:32.031 --> 14:41.045
And I want to suggest that every time you hear a message, the Holy Spirit is planting the seed of God's word in your life, that it might bring forth a harvest.

14:41.085 --> 14:47.474
Jesus mentions that in his parable of the sower and the soil, the seed that fell on

14:47.586 --> 14:55.398
on good soil stands for a person with a good heart who embraces the word and brings forth a crop 30, 60 and 100 fold.

14:56.840 --> 15:05.314
That's the power of the word to produce in us and through us because of the way we receive the word, a harvest of righteousness.

15:06.035 --> 15:08.098
So we should humbly accept it.

15:09.681 --> 15:11.323
How receptive are you to the word of God?

15:12.825 --> 15:14.588
Do you listen to it anytime you can?

15:14.628 --> 15:15.730
Do you desire it?

15:16.610 --> 15:18.352
If you do, your life will be changed.

15:19.814 --> 15:22.358
So how we receive the word of God is half the battle.

15:22.678 --> 15:25.882
The other half is, what do we do with the word of God?

15:26.844 --> 15:28.306
And that's how you and I respond to it.

15:28.326 --> 15:29.668
Look at it in verse 22.

15:30.288 --> 15:34.454
Do not merely listen to the word and so deceive yourselves.

15:35.556 --> 15:43.346
It's interesting, but the word listen there is a word that was used in the ancient world for auditors.

15:44.354 --> 15:47.097
When someone audits a class, what do they do?

15:48.079 --> 15:52.665
They sit and listen because they're only auditing the class.

15:52.985 --> 15:54.547
They don't have to do the assignments.

15:54.587 --> 15:55.969
They don't have to write any papers.

15:55.989 --> 15:57.391
They don't have to take any tests.

15:57.791 --> 16:01.276
They're not responsible for the content that comes their way.

16:03.358 --> 16:09.146
As I read that and think about that, there are a lot of spiritual auditors in the church.

16:10.968 --> 16:12.690
They listen to the word of God

16:13.474 --> 16:18.982
In fact, they've listened to it so much, they can tell you when it's good preaching and when it's not.

16:20.525 --> 16:22.648
But they do nothing with what they hear.

16:24.871 --> 16:30.139
All of us need to be reminded, listening to the word is not an end in itself.

16:30.540 --> 16:42.258
If you come to church simply to hear the word taught, but don't position yourself so the word can change your life, if you don't put it into practice, then you are deceived.

16:44.386 --> 16:47.750
Some say, well, you know, I like to listen because I like to learn.

16:47.770 --> 16:49.332
And I think that's a dangerous thing.

16:49.752 --> 16:50.453
Should we learn?

16:50.513 --> 16:50.813
Yes.

16:51.294 --> 17:04.930
But if our reception of the word and our response to the word stops at listening and learning, then we are in danger of becoming puffed up with pride and becoming a Pharisee.

17:06.892 --> 17:10.396
Paul says in 1 Corinthians chapter eight, knowledge puffs up.

17:11.277 --> 17:12.018
Love builds up.

17:12.706 --> 17:17.672
And when you have knowledge without application, that is a definition.

17:17.832 --> 17:22.578
Spiritual knowledge without application, practical application makes you a Pharisee.

17:24.480 --> 17:32.189
There's a lot of people who can look at truth, know truth, but when you watch their life, they're not applying truth.

17:32.469 --> 17:33.730
They're not in a life group.

17:33.931 --> 17:35.192
They're not on a dream team.

17:35.473 --> 17:36.754
They don't want to serve.

17:39.330 --> 17:42.574
And James is gonna go on in verse 25, 26, 27.

17:42.694 --> 17:48.582
And he's gonna simply say, if you're applying the word of God, it will affect the way you talk.

17:48.843 --> 17:55.812
So if you're a gossip and you know the word of God, something, there's a major disconnect there.

17:56.332 --> 18:06.706
If you know the word of God, but you're not serving the poor and you're not reaching out to help people and you're not active in ministering to people who are hurting, something's wrong there.

18:08.546 --> 18:15.577
The fact is, just because you know the word doesn't mean that you're where you need to be spiritually.

18:15.617 --> 18:21.465
In fact, you're resting in the fact you know the word, but James says you are deceived.

18:23.508 --> 18:28.376
It's in the Greek word that has the idea of a miscalculation.

18:29.397 --> 18:35.346
If you think listening to the word of God is enough, then you've made a major miscalculation.

18:36.258 --> 18:39.862
If you're only a listener and it never impacts your life, you're deceived.

18:39.882 --> 18:41.303
You left something out.

18:41.584 --> 18:42.365
So watch this.

18:42.745 --> 18:46.089
Do not merely listen to the word and so deceive yourself.

18:47.730 --> 18:50.373
Do what it says.

18:51.975 --> 18:55.759
And then to help us understand that, James gives us an illustration.

18:55.799 --> 19:02.066
Anyone who listens to the word, but does not do what it says is like a man who looks at his face in a mirror.

19:02.882 --> 19:10.053
And after looking at himself, he goes away and immediately forgets what he looks like.

19:10.453 --> 19:14.900
The other day, I was, you know, taking care of some last minute things.

19:15.501 --> 19:28.320
I needed, you know, I was thinking about scratch because you don't have to be too particular about your shave, but I knew I needed the shave and the phone rang and I needed to go and I realized as I was driving to the place where I was going that I hadn't shaved.

19:29.321 --> 19:32.466
I looked in the mirror, but I didn't do anything about what I saw.

19:33.474 --> 19:47.076
And the point is when you hear the Word of God and don't do something on the spot that needs to be done, that God is calling you to do through His Word.

19:48.158 --> 19:52.365
You get busy in life, you forget about it, you never get it taken care of.

19:52.385 --> 19:58.194
It's like you looked in the mirror, didn't do anything about what you saw.

19:59.362 --> 20:08.315
When you hear the word of God preached, it always shows you who you are, and it shows us the things in our life that need work.

20:09.537 --> 20:14.484
But the problem for a lot of people, and I just want to say, it's a lot of people don't take notes.

20:16.527 --> 20:19.772
You're not thinking about what God is saying to you, this is the value of notes.

20:21.234 --> 20:29.266
Not only is it helping you to remember what is said, because the shortest pencil is better than the longest memory,

20:30.306 --> 20:40.460
But what happens is, as you're taking the note, you can underline things, you can put an asterisk by it, you can look at it, and you can say, I need to work on this.

20:40.480 --> 20:41.702
You can just write that down.

20:42.323 --> 20:55.762
So the next day on Monday, in your devotional time, you look at it, you say, you know, Lord, you spoke to me yesterday in my heart about this as something that you want me to pay attention to, and you can

20:55.938 --> 20:59.884
Spend time with the Lord asking him to help you to do that in your life.

20:59.904 --> 21:00.905
Lord, what do you want me to do?

21:00.985 --> 21:01.967
How do you want me to do it?

21:02.307 --> 21:04.891
What ministry are you speaking?

21:04.971 --> 21:06.774
How am I going to do this in my life?

21:06.814 --> 21:08.136
What ministry should I be a part of?

21:10.540 --> 21:25.682
And there's things like that that don't happen if you and I just hear the word, walk out of the auditorium and don't have any kind of internal sense of responsibility to do what God is calling us to do.

21:26.562 --> 21:28.324
you've turned away from the mirror.

21:29.665 --> 21:33.849
And there's no benefit in hearing the word and then not doing anything about what you've heard.

21:34.970 --> 21:40.335
So in verse 25, James says, but the man who looks intently into the perfect law that gives freedom.

21:40.416 --> 21:43.078
So this idea is there's an intentionality.

21:44.740 --> 21:55.250
Not only that, but it's interesting because when you consider what a mirror was like back in that day, glass mirrors weren't invented until the 14th century.

21:55.362 --> 22:03.233
a mirror in the ancient world was highly polished, usually bronze, and they would make a mirror out of the bronze.

22:04.434 --> 22:25.202
But you would have to turn it so the light would hit, and you couldn't see your whole face necessarily clearly, so you would have to angle the metal so you could see different parts of your face to get a clear image, and they had to look intently at the mirror, whereas today you can just glance at the mirror.

22:25.378 --> 22:33.932
He's saying, listen, just like people have to intently look at the mirror to examine themselves.

22:35.855 --> 22:41.824
When you and I are looking into the Word of God, the Word of God is like a mirror, and it shows us who we are.

22:41.864 --> 22:43.767
It shows us what we look like spiritually.

22:45.590 --> 22:47.954
It shows us where we're at spiritually.

22:49.570 --> 22:52.112
And the blessing doesn't come in hearing it comes in doing.

22:52.493 --> 23:03.063
Some of you are missing some of the biggest blessings in your life because what happens is your content to hear and God is saying, if you only hear and you don't do, you've missed out on the whole thing.

23:05.024 --> 23:14.653
We have to position ourselves when we read the word, when we hear the word, to make the changes God is convicting us about.

23:15.374 --> 23:19.538
Otherwise we'll miss out on what God wants to do.

23:19.746 --> 23:23.871
wants to bless you.

23:23.891 --> 23:26.154
He wants to do amazing things in your life.

23:27.836 --> 23:36.526
And when we come together as a church, whether it's gathering in person or today online, God is speaking to you right now.

23:36.606 --> 23:40.271
I believe He's speaking to you about how you handle the word, how you listen to the word.

23:43.034 --> 23:49.522
Whether you really give your all to looking intently at the word and examining your life in that moment.

23:51.170 --> 24:00.581
He's calling all of us to a deeper walk with Him that looks at the Word and then applies the Word.

24:02.322 --> 24:07.608
My prayer is that all of us will grow in 2026 and our ability to do that.

24:08.269 --> 24:12.194
Heavenly Father, I thank You because Your Word is true.

24:13.555 --> 24:16.178
And I thank You that as we've heard Your Word today,

24:17.602 --> 24:29.476
The Lord just speaking to every single one of us, may we not just be auditors of the word, but may we actually be intentional in applying the word.

24:31.778 --> 24:42.130
Lord, I pray for those who have been hit and miss in their devotional reading or even reading the Bible at all, that they would recognize the importance

24:43.746 --> 24:58.506
of reading your word, of hearing your voice speak to them through the Word of God, and that all of us would not fall prey to the trap of thinking that somehow, because we heard the message, we've done our duty.

25:00.489 --> 25:04.434
Or because we've learned something new in the message, we got all we needed.

25:05.615 --> 25:13.426
But may we consider every time we hear the Word of God, what is it God that you are calling us to do?

25:14.146 --> 25:15.393
Lord, help us to that end.

25:15.414 --> 25:15.836
I pray.

25:15.876 --> 25:19.538
Father, I thank You for it in Jesus' name.

